SIMPLE: fig_leaf
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fig leaf
<hw>fig leaf</hw> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The leaf from a fig tree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ornamental design shaped like the leaf of a fig
tree, used in architecture; also, a design shaped like a fig leaf to
cover genitalia in sculpture or paintings -- in reference to the
biblical story in Genesis of Adam and Eve, who covered their privates
with fig leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>[figurative]</mark>
<def>Anything used to conceal what is considered embarrassing or
indecent. See sense 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figgum</ent>⟦br⟧
